For Mefisto, nu is the value of the coefficient of Delta u_i, for any i,
where u_i is the i-th component of the velocity.

Cf http://hypertextbook.com/physics/matter/viscosity/

The simple viscosity is noted eta in pascal second [Pa.s]
or millipascal second  [mPa.s]

The kinematic viscosity, noted nu, is the ratio between eta and rho
in square meter per second [m^2/s]
